<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="466" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="5" pageNumber="466">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,429,943,968]" pageId="5" pageNumber="466">Taxonomical notes.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[591,770,943,968]" firstAuthor="Breuning" journalOrPublisher="Geburtstage von Professor Dr. Embrik Strand" pageId="5" pageNumber="466" pagination="180 - 392" part="4" refId="ref6841" refString="Breuning, S. (1938) Novae species Cerambycidarum VI. Festschrift zum 60. Geburtstage von Professor Dr. Embrik Strand, 4, 180 - 392." title="Novae species Cerambycidarum VI. Festschrift zum 60." type="journal article" year="1938">Breuning (1938</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[782,842,944,968]" firstAuthor="Breuning" journalOrPublisher="Novitates Entomologicae, Troisieme Supplement" pageId="5" pageNumber="466" pagination="365 - 526" refId="ref6871" refString="Breuning, S. (1939) Etudes sur les Lamiaires (Coleop. Cerambycidae). Huitieme tribu: Mesosini Thomson. Novitates Entomologicae, Troisieme Supplement, 47 - 66, 365 - 526." title="Etudes sur les Lamiaires (Coleop. Cerambycidae). Huitieme tribu: Mesosini Thomson" type="book chapter" year="1939">1939</bibRefCitation>
), this species has transverse lower eye lobe. It is one of the important characteristics that define the genus. However, on examining the 
<typeStatus box="[1121,1169,981,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="466">type</typeStatus>
material, the length is subequal to width in the male, and slightly longer vertically in the female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="5" pageNumber="466">
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[199,386,1052,1077]" firstAuthor="Breuning" journalOrPublisher="Geburtstage von Professor Dr. Embrik Strand" pageId="5" pageNumber="466" pagination="180 - 392" part="4" refId="ref6841" refString="Breuning, S. (1938) Novae species Cerambycidarum VI. Festschrift zum 60. Geburtstage von Professor Dr. Embrik Strand, 4, 180 - 392." title="Novae species Cerambycidarum VI. Festschrift zum 60." type="journal article" year="1938">
Breuning (
<number box="[320,378,1052,1076]" pageId="5" pageNumber="466" value="1938.0">1938</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
deposited only one 
<typeStatus box="[618,705,1053,1077]" pageId="5" pageNumber="466">syntype</typeStatus>
in 
<collectionCode box="[745,832,1053,1076]" pageId="5" pageNumber="466">BMNH</collectionCode>
, but he referred to sexual dimorphism in the original description. Recently, I found a female specimen deposited in 
<collectionCode box="[852,936,1088,1111]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/kt43-hjs1" name="Museum d'Histoire Naturelle de Bale" pageId="5" pageNumber="466">MHNB</collectionCode>
which has a label handwritten as &quot; 
<typeStatus box="[1326,1428,1088,1112]" pageId="5" pageNumber="466">paratype</typeStatus>
&quot; by Breuning, and it is quite plausible to be another 
<typeStatus box="[798,889,1125,1149]" pageId="5" pageNumber="466">syntype</typeStatus>
. Therefore, I designate the 
<typeStatus box="[1230,1333,1124,1149]" pageId="5" pageNumber="466">lectotype</typeStatus>
and the 
<typeStatus box="[151,302,1159,1184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="466">paralectotype</typeStatus>
as above in order to stabilize the taxonomy and facilitate further identifications of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
